                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d728">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/161: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="#p_GPB1" type="to"
                            >Gilbert</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 11, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>56. Your 139, April 11, 10 a.m. On February 5 and on February 25 the Department
                    requested certain of its offices in Japan and China to extend to the League
                    Commission and to <persName corresp="#p_MMGFR1">General McCoy</persName> all
                    proper assistance. The Department is today sending further supplemental
                    instructions to the Legation at Peiping for transmission to the appropriate
                    consulates.</p>
                <p>You may so inform the Secretary-General.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
